You missed what they said about that I suppose.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Hypothetically, the only alternative to changing abilities such as these would be to inflate every other class up to the same tier of relative power (be it damaging power, or mana regenerative power), then inflate the rest of the world to compensate for the sudden rash of new found power. Drastic, world-wide changes of that sort, however, are a guaranteed way to do more harm than good.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And they are very right.<br>
<br>
These are damned good changes. And they have been needed for a long time.<br>
<br>
Yes, even the monk ac nerf. They wear LEATHER for gods' sake. Leather should never have been anywhere on the same level in mitigating damage as plate.<br>
<br>
The complete heal change doesn't effect the current game much at all. The most buffed hp I've ever heard of is somewhere around 7500(?). So all this really does to the current game, is make it so really high level charmed pets will only be healed 7500 rather then 10000 if chealed. It only greatly effects how PoP will be played, considering the huge hp amounts certain players may have.<br>
<br>
Cheal should have been changed way back in kunark, but it wasn't, so this is the most they can really do without totally reworking the game. <br>
<br>
Better late then never. <p>DiscoWliten<br>
