<br>
Comparing us to others I dont think fairly takes into consideration the spells and other abilities they get. <br>
<br>
Now I am far from saying we should be able to mitigate as well as a warrior, Personally I think our mitigation should fall inbetween a rouge and a warrior. Please do not take in to consideration our avoidance in this and here is why. We get the avoidance for the weight penalty which from what I understand is basicly a 6% improvement over warriors version. Now I know none of you wear leather since you are all chain/plate classes but excluding what you wear try to get your weight under 21 stones just counting the items in your inventory. Then take into consideration that those 21 stones has to include our armor and weapons. I do not fully agree with the nerf since no one yet knows to what extent but I still heavly belive we should fall above rouges in mitigation. Looking at the bases of the 3 melee classes Damage wise order is rouge, monk, warrior. Mitigation wise is warrior, monk, rouge. From what I gather they are talking about droping us below rouges based on the arguement that a chain or plate wearing class should be able to mitigate better then a leather wearing class. Looking at the balance from this perspective that would place monks below rouges in mitigation thus lowering our overall place in the balance of a pure melee class. Before going into the &quot;well i'm a plate wearing (insert class) and should be able to take damage better then you monk. Please take into consideration that there need be some sacrafices to make up for the spells you get. Again I am not saying things are balanced now, but I am saying before you all shout NERF please look at things from a different perspective. <br>
<br>
